      "title": "Resolutions",
      "properties": {
        "source_note_id": 6977,
        "source_note_type": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "# Resolutions\n\n*These notes were written by an LLM, and I encourage you to experiment with resolutions and see what works best for you*\n\n\nWan 2.2 I2V A14B officially targets two area tiers:\n\n## Official 480P tier\n\n- `832x480` landscape\n- `480x832` portrait\n\n## Official 720P tier\n\n- `1280x720` landscape\n- `720x1280` portrait\n\nFor I2V, Wan's official inference treats size as an area target; the output aspect ratio follows the input image. In ComfyUI workflows that expose exact `width` / `height`, use multiples of 16 and stay near the 480P or 720P area tiers.\n\n## 3:4 / Portrait Photo\n\nWan2.2 I2V does not list official 3:4 presets, but this is a common portrait-photo aspect ratio. For I2V, preserving the start image aspect ratio is usually preferable to forcing the official 9:16 portrait preset.\n\nGood ComfyUI 3:4 examples:\n\n- `480x640` conservative 3:4 portrait size, lighter than the official 480P area tier\n- `528x704` balanced 3:4 portrait size, closer to the official 480P area tier\n- `720x960` 3:4 portrait size at a higher area, heavier than the official 480P tier but below square 720P area\n\n\n## 1:1 / Square\n\nWan2.2 I2V does not list official square presets, but official I2V sizing preserves the input image aspect ratio while using the selected 480P or 720P area tier.\n\nGood ComfyUI square examples:\n\n- `624x624` near the official 480P area tier\n- `640x640` common practical square size, slightly above official 480P area\n- `960x960` square equivalent of the official 720P area tier"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
