    {
      "id": 6927,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        -270,
        -1070
      ],
      "size": [
        600,
        1230
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 16,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "Wan Looper Node Settings",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# WAN LOOPER SVI SETTINGS\n\n## SAMPLING\n\n**`steps` / `split_step`**: total denoise steps, then where the HIGH model hands off to the LOW model.\n\n**`control after generate=randomize`** changes `initial_seed` between queued runs. **`seed_mode=fixed`** still reuses that run's `initial_seed` for every segment, which is best for identity and scene stability. **`seed_mode=randomize`** changes later segments.\n\n## SEAMS\n\n**`overlap`**: frames blended at each seam. **`startup_trim`** removes leading frames from segment 2+ before blending. `overlap=5` + `startup_trim=5` is the audit-tested seam baseline; this workflow keeps `trim=0` to preserve all decoded frames.\n\n**`overlap_mode` / `overlap_side`**: KJNodes blend style and seam direction. `linear_blend` + `source` is the normal/default handoff.\n\n## ANCHORS\n\n**Loop Config `anchor_image` is prioritized over all anchor modes for that segment.**\n\n**`anchor_mode=fixed_initial`**: every segment uses the original start image unless a Loop Config supplies `anchor_image`. Extracted anchors are still returned, but they do not drive later segments.\n\n**`anchor_mode=dynamic_every_segment`**: segment 1 uses the start image. Segment 2+ uses the anchor extracted from the previous segment. This is the true rolling-anchor mode.\n\n**`anchor_mode=keyframe_schedule`**: keep using the current scheduled anchor until a listed segment finishes, then promote that segment's extracted anchor for following segments. Example `1,5,7` promotes anchors after segments 1, 5, and 7. The keyframe schedule parameters are ignored unless `anchor_mode=keyframe_schedule`.\n\n**`anchor_frame_offset`** counts backward from the end of the decoded segment. `-1` = final frame. `-5` = fifth frame from the end, which is safer if tail frames are unstable.\n\n**`color_correction`** nudges extracted anchors toward the start image color stats. It matters most when extracted anchors are reused by `dynamic_every_segment` or `keyframe_schedule`; with `fixed_initial` it mainly affects the `last_extracted_anchor` output.\n\n## STITCHING\n\n**`stitch_mode=workflow_style`**: keep the full decoded segment for assembly. **`trim_to_anchor`** cuts each segment after the extracted anchor frame.\n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
